title: Tour De VEISHEA
description:
Join us for a fun day of Mountain Biking at Peterson Park in Story
County. Peterson Park is located approximately 4 miles north of Ames on Hwy
69, then 1.75 miles east on 180th St. This is a NORBA sanctioned event so
participants will need a NORBA license. Daily NORBA licenses may purchased at
the event for $5.
course:
The route consists of approximately 5.1 miles of dirt trail with several climbs, descents, and turns. Number of laps will be determined at race time pertaining to
conditions. The race can be canceled if the race officials declare the course
not fit for race conditions. If the race is canceled, the entry fee will be
refunded.
registration: Register www.veishea.iastate.edu under tournaments and click on tour de veishea
directions:
Peterson Park is located approximately 4 miles north of Ames on Hwy
69, then 1.75 miles east on 180th St.

title: 30th Annual Melon City Criterium

Collegiate SugarBottom Scramble
description: NCCCC collegiate mountain bike race (cross country).
course: 95% single track, 5% gravel/dirt road, technical with some hills.
registration: Registration available on-site the day of the race.
directions: SugarBottom recreation area is located north of North Liberty, IA. From I-380, take Exit 4 (W. Penn St/F28/250th St) East into North Liberty. Continue on Penn Street to Mahaffey Bridge Road. Turn Left onto Mahaffey Bridge Road. SugarBottom recreation area is just past the Mehaffey Bridge on the right. Follow signs to the mountain bike trails.

title: SugarBottom Scramble
description: SugarBottom Scramble is a cross-country mountain bike race and is also the Iowa State Mountain Bike Championships.
course: Course is 90% single track/10% gravel or dirt road. Some sections are technical with rolling hills.
registration: Onsite registration available the day of the race.
notes: Race goes to support ICORR (Iowa Coalition of Off-Road Riders), who maintain and support the SugarBottom mountain bike trails.
directions: Race is located 5 minutes north of North Liberty in the SugarBottom recreation area. From I-380, take Exit 4 (Penn St) towards North Liberty. Turn Left onto Mehaffey Bridge Road. Follow this for approximately 3 miles. SugarBottom recreation area is just across Mehaffey Bridge on the right hand side.
